        <title>[C#]Client-Server networking</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@Lin Lin]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/u/lin">@Lin</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>Use the Socket class.</p>
<p>For servers:</p>
<p><code>ListeningSocket = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.IP);
ListeningSocket.Bind(new IPEndPoint(IPAddress.Any, port));
ListeningSocket.Listen(10000);</code></p>
<p>For clients:</p>
<p><code>Socket socket = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.IP);
socket.Connect("ip", port);</code></p>
<p>There are several guides online. Most will recommend using a TcpListener and TcpClient but I find it more convenient to use a raw socket.</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/t/c-client-server-networking/463848/5">Read full topic</a></p>
